<header class="header">
  <h1>Best Seed Company for Container Vegetables in Cool Climates</h1>
  <p class="tagline">
    The best seeds for containers in cool climates are compact, fast, and reliable.
  </p>
  <p class="lede">
    <strong>For most gardeners, West Coast Seeds and High Mowing Organic Seeds are the best choices for container vegetables in cool climates because they offer compact varieties that perform reliably with limited heat. Johnny’s Selected Seeds is a strong option when you want more control over maturity and variety selection.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Growing vegetables in containers is already more constrained than in-ground gardening. In cooler climates, those constraints stack — less soil volume, less heat, and a shorter growing window.
  </p>
  <p>
    That makes seed choice more important than usual.
  </p>
</header>

